Interface Loadable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Font, Hue.HuePalette, Multi, Multi.Cell, Palette, Skill, SpriteAnimData, SpriteData

    public interface Loadable
    A data structure that may be loaded. This consists of contiguous data. Loadables may be varying in size, but are loadable from a single data source
    Author:
    Kristopher Ives

    • Method Detail

      • load

        void load(ByteBuffer in)
          throws BufferUnderflowException
        Loads this from the provided data source. The position and limit of the buffer will be respected, however the position is not guaranteed to be the limit after invocation.
        Parameters:
        in - the provided data source
        Throws:
        BufferUnderflowException - if not enough data was provided
